1
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:16,133
I thought we were okay now.

2
00:00:16,267 --> 00:00:18,967
But it's so easy for her
to accuse me.

3
00:00:19,100 --> 00:00:22,767
It's connected to her
mother's return.

4
00:00:22,900 --> 00:00:25,633
Eden's confused
again because of her.

5
00:00:25,767 --> 00:00:28,667
I wish we didn't
come back to Manila.

6
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:31,267
If only I knew this
would happen...

7
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:33,633
I wish we didn't
leave the island.

8
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:37,300
I'm the reason her baby died.

9
00:00:37,433 --> 00:00:39,733
I'm not trying to blame
your daughter.

10
00:00:39,867 --> 00:00:41,200
But if she chose to be with you,

11
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:42,500
you were able to care for her...

12
00:00:42,633 --> 00:00:45,667
she could have safely
given birth to her child.

13
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:47,000
Yenyen is not here.

14
00:00:47,133 --> 00:00:51,000
Thank you for taking me in.

15
00:00:51,133 --> 00:00:52,933
Goodbye.

16
00:00:53,067 --> 00:00:53,867
Yenyen!

17
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,200
I thought your family's wealthy.

18
00:00:55,333 --> 00:00:57,433
How come you still haven't
acquired good manners?

19
00:00:57,567 --> 00:00:59,133
We're here to get Yenyen back.

20
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:00,033
Where is she?

21
00:01:00,167 --> 00:01:02,067
Why are you looking
for her here?

22
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:03,600
Is she not here?

23
00:01:03,733 --> 00:01:04,900
Remember this.

24
00:01:05,033 --> 00:01:06,633
If I get to Eden before you do,

25
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:09,400
I will make sure that she won't
be coming back to you.

26
00:01:09,533 --> 00:01:11,800
And your relationship
will be over!

27
00:01:11,933 --> 00:01:13,800
Do you understand?

28
00:01:13,933 --> 00:01:15,400
Get out of here now!

29
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:19,067
I know you talked to her.

30
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:20,633
I'm sure you know where she is.

31
00:01:20,767 --> 00:01:22,067
I have the right to know!

32
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:23,267
I'm still her mom!

33
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:25,400
Are you sure you want to stay
here by yourself?

34
00:01:25,533 --> 00:01:26,600
This island isn't safe
when a typhoon hits.

35
00:01:26,733 --> 00:01:29,900
I've survived all kinds
of trials on this island before.

36
00:01:30,033 --> 00:01:32,133
I need time to be alone.

37
00:01:32,267 --> 00:01:33,100
You know what?

38
00:01:33,233 --> 00:01:35,467
I really don't care
if she disappears!

39
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:36,533
She's so fuzzy.

40
00:01:36,667 --> 00:01:38,467
Eden's full of drama.

41
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:40,467
She's like her mother.

42
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:43,533
She brought us
nothing but trouble.

43
00:01:43,700 --> 00:01:46,333
I'm glad we got rid of the baby.

44
00:01:46,467 --> 00:01:47,033
Mom.

45
00:01:48,333 --> 00:01:50,600
Are you talking about my baby?

46
00:02:09,133 --> 00:02:10,367
Have you been here long?

47
00:02:14,633 --> 00:02:16,233
No, I just arrived.

48
00:02:17,333 --> 00:02:18,367
I was going to talk to you,

49
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:22,000
but I heard you guys say
something about my baby.

50
00:02:22,133 --> 00:02:28,567
Yes, actually, I was saying
that I feel bad for Eden.

51
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:30,500
What she's going
through is not easy.

52
00:02:30,633 --> 00:02:32,600
She just lost the baby.

53
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:35,867
So I guess we all
have to adjust.

54
00:02:37,567 --> 00:02:40,600
We need to be understanding.

55
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:44,600
Yeah, that's what
I'm doing, Mom.

56
00:02:44,733 --> 00:02:47,600
I'm sure I can patch
things up with her.

57
00:02:47,767 --> 00:02:50,133
I just need to
know where she is.

58
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:54,967
I really hope you find her, Son.

59
00:02:57,167 --> 00:02:59,833
You are such a good
boyfriend to her.

60
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:42,133
We're ready for tonight,
even if it gets dark.

61
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,000
I wish you were here, my baby.

62
00:03:55,833 --> 00:03:58,300
This place is so peaceful.

63
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,300
You know what?

64
00:04:04,167 --> 00:04:07,133
I will be happy and content
on this island

65
00:04:07,267 --> 00:04:08,800
as long as you're with me.

66
00:04:11,633 --> 00:04:13,367
You're all I need,
my dear child.

67
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:37,100
Eden's phone is still off.

68
00:04:37,233 --> 00:04:39,900
I didn't get any
information from Raichu.

69
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:43,233
She said Eden didn't tell
her where she was heading.

70
00:04:43,367 --> 00:04:46,600
I guess she knows we'll
all ask Raichu where she is.

71
00:04:46,733 --> 00:04:50,867
She just told Raichu not
to worry because she was safe.

72
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,233
It's good that she's safe.

73
00:04:53,367 --> 00:04:57,467
We should just respect her
decision to get away for a bit.

74
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,967
Until when is she
going to be away?

75
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:01,267
What if she doesn't come back?

76
00:05:01,433 --> 00:05:03,200
Where else can she go?

77
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:05,800
We are her only family.

78
00:05:05,933 --> 00:05:08,567
Amanda, let's just wait
for her to come back, okay?

79
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:15,367
I remember she's been like
that since she was young.

80
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:16,567
She always tries to get away

81
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:21,733
whenever she's sad
or has a problem.

82
00:05:21,867 --> 00:05:24,067
I leave her be.

83
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:26,300
And she always comes
right back, Amanda.

84
00:05:26,433 --> 00:05:28,100
I promise.

85
00:05:28,233 --> 00:05:30,933
After that, she'll be back
to normal.

86
00:05:31,067 --> 00:05:33,600
I just leave her be.

87
00:05:33,733 --> 00:05:36,367
And from then on, I trust
that she'll come back.

88
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,367
So let's leave her be for now.

89
00:05:41,967 --> 00:05:45,433
Let's respect her decision
and give her some space.

90
00:05:45,567 --> 00:05:48,267
I know she'll come back
once she's feeling better.

91
00:06:09,633 --> 00:06:13,100
You know what,
I sometimes miss the island.

92
00:06:13,233 --> 00:06:15,700
That place is so peaceful.

93
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:19,167
We don't have to worry
about anything.

94
00:06:20,833 --> 00:06:22,700
It's as if we're not
in the real world.

95
00:06:22,833 --> 00:06:25,567
I want to forget
all our problems, Red.

96
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:31,567
Who wouldn't go crazy about you?

97
00:09:08,667 --> 00:09:10,533
Goodness, Eden.

98
00:09:10,667 --> 00:09:14,167
You came here to find peace.

99
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:17,067
Not to find someone
who isn't here.

100
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:43,867
Yen.

101
00:10:44,633 --> 00:10:46,133
Yen, wait!

102
00:10:46,433 --> 00:10:47,267
Why are you here?

103
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:48,633
How did you know I'm here?

104
00:10:48,767 --> 00:10:51,333
Even Raichu has no idea
where I am.

105
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:54,100
I just know that
you're here.

106
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:56,400
Because I love you.

107
00:10:58,467 --> 00:11:00,667
I listened to you.

108
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:02,967
And I realized that...

109
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:05,367
this is where you'd go to get
some peace.

110
00:11:08,767 --> 00:11:11,367
Yen, I'm just so happy
that I found you.

111
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:12,900
We were all so
worried about you.

112
00:11:13,033 --> 00:11:14,967
All of us are worried.

113
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:16,733
We even got into an
argument with your mom.

114
00:11:16,867 --> 00:11:19,033
Because we thought
you went back to her.

115
00:11:19,167 --> 00:11:21,567
So, my mom knows that I left?

116
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:25,133
I'm pretty sure she's
looking for you right now.

117
00:11:25,267 --> 00:11:26,433
Why did you have to look for me?

118
00:11:26,567 --> 00:11:28,267
Just leave me be!

119
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:30,200
Yen, wait!

120
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:33,600
So now that you know I'm
okay, can you just leave?

121
00:11:33,733 --> 00:11:36,100
I came here to get
away from all of you.

122
00:11:36,233 --> 00:11:37,000
So please, Red.

123
00:11:37,133 --> 00:11:38,133
Just leave.

124
00:11:40,267 --> 00:11:42,000
Yen, wait.

125
00:11:46,267 --> 00:11:47,633
I checked the whole house.

126
00:11:47,767 --> 00:11:49,233
Sir Red is not here.

127
00:11:50,867 --> 00:11:53,233
I'm sure he went
out to find Eden.

128
00:11:54,867 --> 00:11:56,467
He's not picking up!

129
00:11:58,733 --> 00:12:01,367
It's so unlike Red.

130
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:05,767
He would answer because
he knows I'm worried about him.

131
00:12:05,900 --> 00:12:07,633
I'm sure his phone died.

132
00:12:07,767 --> 00:12:08,867
Or something like that.

133
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,567
I called Zandro.

134
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:15,500
I asked him to help us find Red.

135
00:12:15,667 --> 00:12:19,067
If something bad happens to my
son while looking for Eden,

136
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:20,333
I will make her pay.

137
00:12:20,467 --> 00:12:25,567
Oh my. How she wishes that she'd
moved back to her mother!

138
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:56,967
Sir, the wind is starting
to blow hard.

139
00:12:57,100 --> 00:12:59,333
We should get out of here before
the rain starts to pour down.

140
00:12:59,467 --> 00:13:01,733
Go and call her.

141
00:13:01,867 --> 00:13:03,367
Okay, I'll talk to her.

142
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:04,567
Wait here.

143
00:13:08,733 --> 00:13:11,467
Yen, we have to leave.

144
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:13,200
He said it was about to rain.

145
00:13:13,333 --> 00:13:13,867
What rain are you talking about?

146
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,967
It's so sunny out.

147
00:13:16,100 --> 00:13:16,933
You should go.

148
00:13:18,333 --> 00:13:20,267
Do you see that dark clouds?

149
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:21,567
It's coming this way.

150
00:13:23,267 --> 00:13:24,833
Just go.

151
00:13:24,967 --> 00:13:27,033
I'm not leaving without you.

152
00:13:28,533 --> 00:13:30,667
I'll go ahead if you
guys don't want to leave.

153
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:32,033
I'll come back
for you tomorrow.

154
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:36,367
Why are you so stubborn?

155
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:38,567
I came here to find peace.

156
00:13:38,700 --> 00:13:41,833
And I won't get it
if you're here.

157
00:13:41,967 --> 00:13:42,933
So stubborn!

158
00:13:43,067 --> 00:13:46,133
No, I'm staying with you.

159
00:13:46,267 --> 00:13:49,233
Yen, let's just use
this time to talk.

160
00:13:49,367 --> 00:13:52,600
I have a lot to tell you
about the video you saw.

161
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:57,567
Suit yourself.

162
00:14:01,933 --> 00:14:02,767
Okay.

163
00:14:02,900 --> 00:14:05,033
Yen, I have nowhere to go.

164
00:14:05,167 --> 00:14:06,133
I'll stay right here.

165
00:14:06,267 --> 00:14:07,533
I'll be here until you
decide to talk to me.

166
00:14:07,667 --> 00:14:08,667
I'm not going anywhere.

167
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:19,667
Rina, is your husband here?

168
00:14:20,767 --> 00:14:22,367
He went to the bank.

169
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:27,067
I don't know how he can still
work while Red is missing.

170
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,367
Relax, Rina.

171
00:14:28,533 --> 00:14:31,333
Someone told me they
saw Red at the airport.

172
00:14:31,467 --> 00:14:32,867
I don't know which
flight he's on.

173
00:14:34,033 --> 00:14:35,033
Airport?

174
00:14:36,367 --> 00:14:38,700
Where is he going?

175
00:14:38,833 --> 00:14:41,767
Rina, stop worrying
about your son.

176
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:43,267
He can handle himself.

177
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:46,600
You better think about
what is going to happen tonight.

178
00:14:46,733 --> 00:14:48,100
Because I already know
where that fool

179
00:14:48,233 --> 00:14:49,367
who cheated us is hiding.

180
00:14:55,633 --> 00:14:59,833
Now I can get my
revenge on that monster.

181
00:15:35,700 --> 00:15:38,833
Are you going to
let me in now?

182
00:15:38,967 --> 00:15:40,833
Are you going to wait
for an invitation?

183
00:15:42,467 --> 00:15:43,167
Are you sure?

184
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,300
I'm soaking wet.

185
00:15:45,433 --> 00:15:47,800
Your tent might get
wet if I come inside.

186
00:15:47,933 --> 00:15:49,333
Get inside.

187
00:16:03,533 --> 00:16:04,633
Lucho!

188
00:16:04,767 --> 00:16:05,533
Help!

189
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:07,100
Lucho!

190
00:16:07,933 --> 00:16:08,800
Lucho!

191
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:10,433
Lucho!

192
00:16:13,067 --> 00:16:13,800
No!

193
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:16,233
No!
No!

194
00:16:17,667 --> 00:16:18,400
No!

195
00:16:18,533 --> 00:16:19,467
Get in the car!

196
00:16:55,100 --> 00:16:56,300
What are you doing?

197
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:00,467
I just touched your face.

198
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:03,833
I just fell asleep and you're
taking advantage already!

199
00:17:05,133 --> 00:17:06,733
Taking advantage?

200
00:17:06,867 --> 00:17:08,933
You were hugging me.

201
00:17:09,067 --> 00:17:10,667
Oh, really?

202
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,767
I don't buy it.

203
00:17:13,767 --> 00:17:14,867
It stopped raining.

204
00:17:15,033 --> 00:17:16,267
You can leave tomorrow.

205
00:18:00,767 --> 00:18:03,067
This is the place.

206
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:06,033
This is where Rina and Zandro
tortured me.

207
00:18:08,733 --> 00:18:13,267
I'm sure this is where they
bring the people who owe them.

208
00:18:15,967 --> 00:18:17,300
This place is well-hidden.

209
00:18:17,433 --> 00:18:19,167
That's why they
don't need security.

210
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:21,067
It's better for us.

211
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:22,500
It will make things
easier for us.

212
00:18:35,567 --> 00:18:37,400
Just stay here for now.

213
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:41,233
You don't need to come inside if
you can't handle it yet, okay?

214
00:18:56,467 --> 00:18:58,433
Yen, please talk to me.

215
00:18:58,567 --> 00:19:01,200
Stop pretending you don't
feel anything for me anymore.

216
00:19:02,467 --> 00:19:03,933
You came back here...

217
00:19:04,067 --> 00:19:05,767
to the place where
we first met...

218
00:19:05,900 --> 00:19:07,300
where we started
our relationship.

219
00:19:07,433 --> 00:19:09,000
So it means you still love me.

220
00:19:09,133 --> 00:19:11,733
Yes, I came back here.

221
00:19:11,867 --> 00:19:14,300
Because I want to return
to how we used to be.

222
00:19:14,433 --> 00:19:17,500
But we're not the
same people anymore.

223
00:19:17,633 --> 00:19:19,533
A lot has happened, Red.

224
00:19:19,667 --> 00:19:22,267
We can't go back
to how we used to be.

225
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,833
That's not true!

226
00:19:23,967 --> 00:19:25,100
Here.

227
00:19:25,233 --> 00:19:26,500
Give me a chance to
explain everything.

228
00:19:26,633 --> 00:19:28,467
This can fix our
relationship, Yen.

229
00:19:28,633 --> 00:19:29,533
Can you knock it off?

230
00:19:29,667 --> 00:19:31,533
Do you think
we'll get back together

231
00:19:31,667 --> 00:19:33,100
just because we're back
on this island?

232
00:19:33,233 --> 00:19:34,600
Do you think I'll give
in after you show me

233
00:19:34,733 --> 00:19:36,600
a little affection?

234
00:19:36,733 --> 00:19:38,200
Come on, Red.
That will never happen.

235
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:39,533
Can you leave?

236
00:19:44,900 --> 00:19:45,200
Red!

237
00:19:46,367 --> 00:19:47,233
Sorry!

238
00:19:48,233 --> 00:19:49,333
You burned your hand!

239
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:53,900
Come on. I have a first aid kit
in the tent.

240
00:19:54,033 --> 00:19:54,633
Let's go.

241
00:19:55,700 --> 00:19:57,233
Sorry.

242
00:20:12,133 --> 00:20:16,100
It's all set. I installed
the cameras and CCTVs.

243
00:20:16,233 --> 00:20:18,633
We just have to wait
for them to come back

244
00:20:18,767 --> 00:20:21,400
and bring in new victims.

245
00:20:25,267 --> 00:20:26,967
I was nervous, Lucho.

246
00:20:28,433 --> 00:20:30,867
I know we're about to stop
Rina from her misdeeds.

247
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:33,767
But I'm scared of
what might happen.

248
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:38,267
I wish we could get this done
without people getting hurt.

249
00:20:39,833 --> 00:20:40,900
Don't worry.

250
00:20:42,167 --> 00:20:44,100
If our plans work,

251
00:20:44,233 --> 00:20:46,633
this will be the last time
they can hurt somebody.

252
00:20:50,167 --> 00:20:50,967
Let's go.

253
00:21:04,167 --> 00:21:06,000
Where else does it hurt?

254
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:09,233
Right here.

255
00:21:13,267 --> 00:21:15,267
Sorry, I know it's corny.

256
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:17,133
But it's true.

257
00:21:17,267 --> 00:21:18,367
That will be your last.

258
00:21:22,167 --> 00:21:26,667
Do you remember the first
time we made a fire?

259
00:21:36,867 --> 00:21:39,933
We were so happy back then.

260
00:21:40,067 --> 00:21:41,833
I almost kissed you.

261
00:21:42,900 --> 00:21:44,200
Do you remember that?

262
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:49,500
Yen, let's not waste everything

263
00:21:49,633 --> 00:21:51,533
we've been through together.

264
00:21:54,767 --> 00:21:59,167
I don't know if we can
move on, Red.

265
00:21:59,300 --> 00:22:02,767
Because no matter what I do,
I can't get it out of my mind.

266
00:22:02,900 --> 00:22:05,433
I can't forget
everything you said.

267
00:22:05,567 --> 00:22:08,733
Sabina edited the video, Yen.

268
00:22:08,867 --> 00:22:09,667
Here, this is what
really happened.

269
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:10,800
You have to see all of it.

270
00:22:10,933 --> 00:22:11,900
I don't want to hear it again.

271
00:22:12,033 --> 00:22:13,100
Just, please, watch this.

272
00:22:13,233 --> 00:22:14,100
Come on.

273
00:22:14,233 --> 00:22:15,267
Please, do this for me.

274
00:22:17,233 --> 00:22:18,433
Wait, wait!

275
00:22:18,567 --> 00:22:20,100
Let's take a video.

276
00:22:20,233 --> 00:22:22,367
Come on, let's
remember this night.

277
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:23,100
Let's go!

278
00:22:23,233 --> 00:22:24,467
Come on!

279
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:28,567
I don't have to change diapers.

280
00:22:28,700 --> 00:22:30,433
No baby bottles.

281
00:22:32,300 --> 00:22:34,167
Because my baby's gone.

282
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,400
I thought we could overcome
everything

283
00:22:37,533 --> 00:22:39,967
as long as we were together.

284
00:22:40,100 --> 00:22:42,067
Because that's what we
promised each other.

285
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:46,300
We promised each other
that we would never be apart.

286
00:22:46,433 --> 00:22:48,933
That we'd always be together.

287
00:22:49,100 --> 00:22:50,000
Red!

288
00:22:50,133 --> 00:22:51,667
I'm sorry!

289
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:53,333
I'm sorry.

290
00:22:59,167 --> 00:22:59,833
Go on!

291
00:23:06,867 --> 00:23:09,633
We don't need to wait too long.

292
00:23:09,767 --> 00:23:11,500
We have the evidence
against them now.

293
00:23:13,767 --> 00:23:15,833
Rina's a monster.

294
00:23:15,967 --> 00:23:17,633
Let's report them to the police!

295
00:23:19,267 --> 00:23:20,400
Go on!

296
00:23:22,567 --> 00:23:25,633
Rina's face is not shown
on the CCTV.

297
00:23:27,700 --> 00:23:29,300
Have mercy on this poor guy.

298
00:23:29,433 --> 00:23:31,233
Even if we don't know him,

299
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:35,300
he doesn't deserve
this treatment!

300
00:23:35,433 --> 00:23:36,867
Are you ready to confess now?

301
00:23:38,367 --> 00:23:39,267
I don't know anything!

302
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:40,867
What do you mean by you
don't know anything?

303
00:23:42,500 --> 00:23:43,533
Tell me the truth!

304
00:23:44,800 --> 00:23:46,200
Confess now!

305
00:23:46,333 --> 00:23:47,733
- Who told you to do it?
- It's Elmer.

306
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,233
We have to help him.

307
00:23:51,533 --> 00:23:52,333
Let's go.

308
00:23:54,667 --> 00:23:57,533
You are my first and last love.

309
00:23:58,400 --> 00:24:02,633
I don't want to be with
anyone else my entire life.

310
00:24:02,767 --> 00:24:05,233
You're my greatest
love, Yenyen.

311
00:24:06,033 --> 00:24:10,133
And I want to spend the
rest of my life loving you.

312
00:24:10,267 --> 00:24:12,567
I wish we could
stay here forever.

313
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:14,500
I like that idea.

314
00:24:14,633 --> 00:24:18,067
But we have to go
back to our families.

315
00:24:19,933 --> 00:24:20,700
Hey!

316
00:24:21,933 --> 00:24:23,333
Stop this!

317
00:24:23,467 --> 00:24:24,533
Put your gun down.

318
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:26,767
Zandro.

319
00:24:28,867 --> 00:24:30,167
Take your mask off.

320
00:24:32,767 --> 00:24:33,867
I knew it was you, Rina.

321
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:35,300
I just want to
see your face.

322
00:24:35,433 --> 00:24:40,067
I'm happy because I'm
on this island with you.

323
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:40,933
Me too, Yen.

324
00:24:42,267 --> 00:24:44,167
I'm so happy that
I'm with you.

325
00:24:45,833 --> 00:24:47,833
I will never leave you.
